0009|- [HelpText]
0010|*In addition to control words in brackets [], control lines
0011|*(with a '-' in the control column) can hold genuine PostScript
0012|*code.
0013|*For example, the following PRINT scheme produces a gray 3 cm x 3 cm
0014|*square:
0015|* 11 *PRINT 12,19
0016|* 12 - include PS.DEV / not necessary if PS.DEV is default in SURVO.APU
0017|* 13 *A shaded square:
0018|* 14 & 7 (empty lines to have space for the square)
S   |     &
0019|* 15 - /edge 3 2.54 div 72 mul def[LF]
0020|* 16 - gsave currentpoint newpath moveto edge 0 rlineto 0 edge rlineto[LF]
0021|* 17 - edge neg 0 rlineto closepath 0.5 setgray fill grestore[LF]
0022|* 18 *
0023|* 19 *The story continues...
0025|*Please, note that lines 15-17 containing pure PostScript code have to
0026|*be terminated by line feeds defined as [LF] in PS.DEV .
0027|*Also the brackets [] appearing in PostScript arrays have to be replaced
0028|*by control codes [LB] for '[' and [RB] for ']'.
0029|*Otherwise PostScript code can be written in print lists in a normal way.
