0056|- [HelpText]
0057|*The default setting (in PS.DEV) is a standard A4 sheet in upright
0058|*(portrait position). By [LANDSCAPE] the page will be rotated 90 degrees
0059|*to landscape orintation. Thereafter [PORTRAIT] will restore the original
0060|*portrait orientation. If [LANDSCAPE] is used for consecutive pages, it
0061|*is the user's responsibility to alter (diminish) the page length (set
0062|*by [page_length(x)] where x is given in points.)
0064|*In PRINT also control words [HOME(x,y)], [SCALING(kx,ky)], and
0065|*[ROTATION(angle)] can be used to achieve an arbitrary location, scaling,
0066|*and rotation of the output on the current page. Default settings are
0067|*[HOME(0,0)]     (physical left-bottom corner of the paper)
0068|*[SCALING(1,1)]
0069|*[ROTATION(0)]
