0085|- [HelpText]
0086|*The units used for scaling and locating text and pictures in
0087|*Survo PostScript applications are:
0089|*  1 point = 1/72 inches
0090|*            used in font sizes, line spacing and page length.
0091|*            It is also the basic unit in the user coordinate system.
0092|*  1 pica  = 1/12 inches = 6 points
0093|*            used in marginal setting (by [left_margin(x)]) and in
0094|*            printing width (by [trim(x)]).
0095|*  1 dmm   = 0.1 mm
0096|*            is the unit for all measurements related to Survo
0097|*            graphics. Also coordinates of pictures when locating them
0098|*            in PRINT (by - picture control lines) are given in dmm.
