0106|- [HelpText]
0107|*Original PostScript does not have codes for accented characters (like
0108|*Ñ,î) and other special text characters used in various languages, but it
0109|*has predetermined names for them (Ñ is adieresis, for example).
0110|*Each application system has to encode selected characters. The current
0111|*version of PS.DEV does so for all scandinavian characters (Ñ,î,Ü,é,ô,è)
0112|*by giving them the same ASCII codes as used in the IBM PC.
0113|*The user can extend and alter the set of special characters by editing
0114|*PS.DEV. By listing this file, it is very easy to find the current setting
0115|*and alter the selection according to one's needs.
