0186|- [HelpText]
0187|#EPS <PSfile>,<EPSfile>
S   |     <      > <       >
0188|*converts a Survo PostScript file made by PLOT with DEVICE=PS,<PSfile>
S   |                                                              <      >
0189|*into an Encapsulated PostScript file <EPSfile>. The output file can be
S   |                                      <       >
0190|*used in several other desktop publishing programs as such.
0192|*Also PostScript files consisting of one page only and generated by the
0193|*PRINT operation of Survo can be converted. However, the PRINT list
0194|*must then include a `- %Survo Graphics END[LF]' line as follows:
0195|* *PRINT CUR+1,E TO <PSfile>
S   |                    <      >
0196|* *<text and graphics to be printed on one page>
S   |   <                                           >
0197|* -  %Survo Graphics END[LF]
0198|* E
0200|*The EPS file will include comment lines according to the Encapsulated
0201|*PostScript Files Specification Version 2.0 by Adobe Systems.
0203|*The default comments given by the EPS operation can be replaced by
0204|*using following specifications (default values given):
0205|*   VERSION_COMMENT=%!PS-Adobe-2.0_EPSF-2.0
0206|*   TITLE=Survo_PostScript_file
0207|*   CREATOR=
0208|*   CREATION_DATE=<current_date>
S   |                  <            >
0209|*   BOUNDINGBOX=<values_obtained_on_the basis_of_HOME_and_SIZE>
S   |                <                                             >
0210|*                 given in 0.1 mm units and converted automatically
0211|*                 into Points.
0212|*   DOCUMENT_FONTS=
0214|*The BoundingBox comment is automatically generated.
