0243|- [HelpText]
0244|#EPS JOIN <target.ps>,A1,A2,A3,...
S   |          <         >
0245|*         A1=<file1.ps>,<x1>,<y1>,<kx1>,<ky1>
S   |             <        > <  > <  > <   > <   >
0246|*         A2=<file2.ps>,<x2>,<y2>,<kx2>,<ky2>
S   |             <        > <  > <  > <   > <   >
0247|*         A3=<file3.ps>,<x3>,<y3>,<kx3>,<ky3>
S   |             <        > <  > <  > <   > <   >
0248|*         ...
0249|*combines several Survo PostScript files made by PLOT operations into
0250|*one Survo PostScript file <target.ps>. Such target files can be combined
S   |                           <         >
0251|*again by EPS JOIN and included in PRINT lists by  - picture  control
0252|*lines.
0253|*Files to be combined are referred to by any names (as A1,A2,A3,.. above)
0254|*in the EPS JOIN command. Each item must have a corresponding
0255|*specification giving the PS file name and relative x and y coordinates
0256|*of the left low corner of the graph. Default is <x>=<y>=0.
S   |                                                 < > < >
0257|*Also individual scaling coefficients can be given. Default is <kx>=<ky>=1.
S   |                                                               <  > <  >
0258|*The target file is not an EPS file, but it can be converted to such one
0259|*by EPS <target.ps>,<EPSfile> .
S   |        <         > <       >
0261|- [New]
0262|*EPS JOIN2 <target.ps>,A1,A2,A3,...
S   |           <         >
0263|*does the same job but also adjusts the bounding box in non-overlapping case.
